<heading id="894481FBFFD9FFF5A1E87E0C92AC0F1E" box="[225,716,1366,1391]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="16" pageNumber="1228" reason="8">
FAMILY 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFD9FFF5A0347E0C92AC0F1E" authority="BERRY, 1914" authorityName="BERRY" authorityYear="1914" box="[317,716,1366,1391]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Lampadioteuthidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="16" pageNumber="1228" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">
LAMPADIOTEUTHIDAE 
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFD9FFF5A3337E0C92AC0F1E" author="Berry SS" box="[570,716,1366,1391]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1228" pagination="134 - 149" refId="ref14181" refString="Berry SS. 1914. Notes on a collection of cephalopods from the Kermadec Islands. Transactions and Proceedings of the New Zealand Institute 46: 134 - 149." type="journal article" year="1914">BERRY, 1914</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFD9FFF5A08D7E2792490FE7" blockId="16.[388,553,1405,1430]" box="[388,553,1405,1430]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1228">(ONE SPECIES)</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9AA9651CFFD9FFF5A1AA7EFC93970B05" pageId="16" pageNumber="1228" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFD9FFF5A1AA7EFC92440CBE" blockId="16.[163,779,1446,1744]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1228">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFD9FFF5A1AA7EFC91530FCA" box="[163,307,1446,1467]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1228">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Small adult-sized and colourful 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFD9FFF5A1AA7E9E910C0FAB" authorityName="PFEFFER" authorityYear="1900" box="[163,364,1476,1498]" class="Cephalopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="16" pageNumber="1227" phylum="Mollusca" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Enoploteuthoidea">Enoploteuthoidea</taxonomicName>
with four ocular and five tentacular photophores (the most proximal stalked near the base of the tentacle), plus anal, branchial and posteroabdominal photophores, branchial photophores transversally elongated, without central abdominal photophore; rostrum in gladius; without hooks on arms and tentacles; right ventral arm hectocotylized with enlarged protective membrane in the mid-arm; males with single terminal organ.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFD9FFF5A1AA7DA293970B05" blockId="16.[163,778,1784,1898]" lastBlockId="16.[827,1444,197,372]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1228">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFD9FFF5A1AA7DA2917A0D7C" box="[163,282,1784,1805]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1228">Remarks:</emphasis>
This group has a complex taxonomic history (see 
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFD9FFF5A0407C4D92C30D5D" author="Vecchione M &amp; Young RE" box="[329,675,1815,1837]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1228" refId="ref17498" refString="Vecchione M, Young RE. 2019 a. Lycoteuthidae Pfeffer, 1908. Version 26 March 2019. Available at: http: // tolweb. org / Lycote uthidae / 19636 / 2019.03.26" type="url" year="2019">Vecchione &amp; Young, 2019a</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFD9FFF5A3CB7C4D90910D3D" author="Berry SS" pageId="16" pageNumber="1228" pagination="134 - 149" refId="ref14181" refString="Berry SS. 1914. Notes on a collection of cephalopods from the Kermadec Islands. Transactions and Proceedings of the New Zealand Institute 46: 134 - 149." type="journal article" year="1914">Berry (1914)</bibRefCitation>
erected this monotypic family, but it was later included as the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFD9FFF5A3297C0E93A80AAB" authority="Berry, 1914" authorityName="Berry" authorityYear="1914" box="[544,968,197,1898]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Lycoteuthidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="16" pageNumber="1228" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Lampadioteuthinae">
Lampadioteuthinae 
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFD9FFF5A2327B9C93A80AAB" author="Berry SS" box="[827,968,197,219]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1228" pagination="134 - 149" refId="ref14181" refString="Berry SS. 1914. Notes on a collection of cephalopods from the Kermadec Islands. Transactions and Proceedings of the New Zealand Institute 46: 134 - 149." type="journal article" year="1914">Berry, 1914</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
within 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFD9FFF5A5257B9F94BB0AAA" authorityName="Pfeffer" authorityYear="1908" box="[1068,1243,197,219]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Lycoteuthidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="16" pageNumber="1228" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Lycoteuthidae</taxonomicName>
by Naef (1923). 
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFD9FFF5A2327BBE93A30A8B" author="Voss GL" box="[827,963,228,250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1228" pagination="85 - 178" refId="ref17730" refString="Voss GL. 1956. A review of the cephalopods of the Gulf of Mexico. Bulletin of Marine Science of the Gulf and Caribbean 6: 85 - 178." type="journal article" year="1956">Voss (1956)</bibRefCitation>
maintained them as separated families in an initial article. He then considered them to occur within the same family in a subsequent article (
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFD9FFF5A4607A7893140B27" author="Voss GL" pageId="16" pageNumber="1228" pagination="264 - 305" refId="ref17815" refString="Voss GL. 1962. A monograph of the Cephalopoda of the North Atlantic. I. The family Lycoteuthidae. Bulletin of Marine Science of the Gulf and Caribbean 12: 264 - 305." type="journal article" year="1962">Voss, 1962</bibRefCitation>
). The results provided here support a familylevel treatment.
</paragraph>
